<div></div><p><b>The Internet was created in early 1990's and contains 30 Billion Pages.</b></p></div>
<div><ul style="list-style-type:circle"><p><b>Major Pieces of the Internet:</b></p>
  <li><p><b><em>1) You/your computer/ your browser</b></em></p></li>
  <li><p><b><em>2) the internet</b></em></p></li>
  <li><p><b><em>3) Servers</b></p></em></li></ul></div>

div><dl><p><b>HTML is made up of:</b></p>
  <dt><p><b>Text content</b> - <dd><em>what you see</em></p></dd></dt>
  <dt><p><b>Markup</b><em> - <dd>what it looks like</em></p></dd></dt>
<dt><p><b>References to other documents</b><em>- <dd>eg images and videos</em></p></dd></dt>
<dt><p><b>Links to other pages</b></p></dt></div>

<div><p><b>HTML MARKUP:</b></p>
<p><b>Opening Tag, Content, Closing Tag all of which is known as an Element</b></p>
<p><b>b = bold</b></p>
<p><b>em = emphasis -italics</b></p></div

<div><p><b>HTML ATTRIBUTES:</b></p>
<p><b>ATTR</b> = "value"</p>
<p><b>Anchor</b> = a = used for making links</p>
<p><b>Images</b> = IMG img src="url"  alt= "txt"</p>
<p><b>alt</b>= alternate  text to be displayed if image doesn't load</p>
<p><b>br</b> = break  inline command</p>
<b>p </b>= paragraph  block command<p></p>

<p><b>Span</b> = inline</p>
<p><b>Div</b> = block command</p><br></div>

<div><ul style="list-style-type:square"><b>FIVE IMPORTANT THINGS TO TAKE AWAY FROM LESSON ONE:</b><li><dl><dt><b>What a Web Page is-</b></dt><dd> a text doc written in HTML. Web browsers read these documents and interpret them.</dd></dl></li>
  <li><dl><dt><b>How Coding works-</b></dt><dd>When programmers write text in a language that a computer can understand and then follow the instructions.</dd></dl></li>
  <li><b>Computers Are Stupid</li></b><br>
<li><b>Programmers Cannot Remember Everything</li></b>
<li><dl><dt><b>Basic HTML Vocabulary</b> -</dt><dd> Tags are always contained within bullets.</dd>
  <dd>Element is everything inside opening/closing tags.</dd>
  <dd>Attribute is the property of the HTML Element.</dd><br><br></div>
  
  
<div><b>Lesson 1.2: Creating a Structured Document</b><br>
 HTML files are like the walls of a house dividing rooms.<br> CSS is like the style of your house, colour, design,v etc.<br> Javascript is your interactive components.<br> Webtools are used to build a webpage.<br><br><b> Wikipedia's Page Structure:<br></b> Not all elements are visible.<br> All elements are rectangular<br> You can read the same texts as on the page<br> HTML and CSS are languages<br>HTML controls the structure of a Wepage<br>CSS controls the style or appearance <br> DOM is Document Object Model which is the tree-like structure of a page<br>HTML=language with syntax and rules<br>Tag is an element in a tree, i.e. DOM<br> CSS allows us to use a syntax/rules to change the look and style<br><br><br><br></div>
 
 
 